    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This driver-spec 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a mechanically sound example of the iconic S54B32 platform. The 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six features individual throttle bodies and high-pressure dual-VANOS, providing exceptional throttle response and a linear power band up to the 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered through a tactile 6-speed manual gearbox to the rear wheels via a factory limited-slip differential. Maintenance is current, including a cooling system refresh and a thorough inspection of the rear subframe mounting points. The suspension retains its communicative feedback with tight bushings and responsive damping. While the aesthetics show a light patina consistent with its age, the drivetrain remains potent and the chassis is structurally rigid, making it an ideal candidate for the spirited purist.",
      "price": 33500.0,
